  <div class="container top-spacer">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header display-4 text-center">
        About Wecasual
      </div>
      <div class="card-body about-text">
        <h3 class="card-title">The spirit of real life recreational sport leagues brought to eSports</h3>
        <ul class="card-text">
          <li>Wecasual is a Dota 2 community that <span class="font-weight-bold">hosts leagues and pick-up games</span> for players looking to have a fun and positive Dota 2 experience.</li>
          <li>Wecasual is a <span class="font-weight-bold">toxic-player free environment</span> where players can play with a consistent team every week in our leagues and also
              participate in pick-up style games for those who want to play even more.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="card-title">How does Wecasual work?</h3>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>To participate in the Wecasual community there is <span class="font-weight-bold">$5/month subscription</span>.</li>
            <li>Once you join Wecasual you will have <span class="font-weight-bold">a team to play 2 weekly games with</span>.</li>
            <li>Wecasual league games are Monday through Thursday at 9:00 PM EST.</li>
            <li>There is no prize pool and there are no individual player rankings; Wecasual is strictly for those looking to hang out
            with friends and enjoy playing their games.</li>
            <li>In addition to weekly games with a team there are tons of <span class="font-weight-bold">pick-up games</span> like inhouse games and mini-tournaments.
              <ul>
                <li><i>Pick-up games are signed up for on an individual basis.</i></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Players can <span class="font-weight-bold">join solo or join with friends!</span> If you are solo or need more players to round out your stack,
            don’t worry, we will find you a team or fill in any remaining spots for you.</li>
            <li>Because Wecasual focuses on fun and social play players are not expected to have set roles (eg. mid, support, etc…). Teams are expected to have players swapping positions.</li>
          </ul>

        <h3 class="card-title">Who is Wecasual for?</h3>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>We are looking for casual players whose primary objective is to have fun playing Dota 2.</li>
            <li>Our community is open to all players who are <b>less than 4k MMR </b> (Case by case exceptions can be made).</li>
            <li>Other than that, anyway can join Wecasual, as long as you are friendly person.</li>
            <li>         We strongly encourage <span class="font-weight-bold">newer players</span> to join!</li>

          </ul>

        <h3 class="card-title">It's more than just Dota 2</h3>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>At Wecasual it is not just about playing Dota 2. Wecasual is the place to <span class="font-weight-bold">unwind and chill</span> out for people who love Dota 2.</li>
            <li>Before and after every game we offer activities to encourage players to <span class="font-weight-bold">hangout in our Discord</span> with their team and other teams too.</li>
          </ul>
          <h3 class="card-title">Discord Link</h3>
